			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Perboric acid is a chemical compound known for its bleaching and oxidizing properties. It is often used in the formulation of detergents, cleaning products, and as a bleaching agent in some industrial processes. The product flow details would specify its purity, form (e.g., powder, liquid), concentration, grade, and compliance with relevant industrial standards. The product flow would indicate if it has been processed, packaged, and how it is made available to the consumer or delivered to the production plant.</common:generalComment>
